    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STOPMASTER WEDGE TYPE BRAKE - SERVICE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>SERVICE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="1">
            <title>CHAMFERED BRAKE DRUM</title>
            <para>A chamfer has been added on the brake drum on the inside outer edge to aid in removal when brake
                service is necessary. The chamfer allows the brake lining to overlap the drum edge (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401318">Figure 18</hotlnk>). This, in turn, prevents the development of scored wear
                rings on I.D. of the drum, which could interfere with disassembly.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0401318" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg04/G0401318.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Chamfered Drum</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BRAKE DRUM</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. 1/16 INCH (1.588 MM) OVERLAP</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LINING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
